---

<AdminLayout
  title="Carousel"
  description="A powerful and flexible slideshow component for cycling through elements"
  currentPath="docs/interface/carousel"
  enableComponentPreview={true}
>
  <PageHeader {...pageHeaderConfig} />
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-9 order-1 order-lg-0">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <p class="my-0">
            A carousel is a dynamic slideshow component that cycles through elements, perfect for
            showcasing featured content, product highlights, or important announcements. With
            support for images, captions, and multiple transition styles, carousels offer an
            engaging way to present sequential content to users.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row js-toc-content">
        <div class="col-12">
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="basic-example">Basic Example</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              The basic carousel features a simple slideshow with navigation controls. It includes
              multiple slides within the <code>carousel-inner</code> container and navigation buttons
              for manual control. The first slide is marked as <code>active</code> to indicate the starting
              position.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Basic Carousel"
              height="450px"
              component={basicCarouselExample}
              htmlCode={basicCarouselExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="indicators">Indicators</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Add slide indicators to your carousel using the <code>carousel-indicators</code> class.
              These clickable indicators show the current slide position and allow direct navigation
              to specific slides. Each indicator corresponds to a slide in the sequence.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Carousel with Indicators"
              height="450px"
              component={carouselWithIndicatorsExample}
              htmlCode={carouselWithIndicatorsExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="captions">Captions</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Enhance your carousel slides with descriptive captions using the <code
                >carousel-caption</code
              > class. Captions can include headings, paragraphs, and other text content to provide context
              for each slide. They're hidden on mobile devices by default using the <code
                >d-none d-md-block</code
              > classes.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Carousel with Captions"
              height="450px"
              component={carouselWithCaptionsExample}
              htmlCode={carouselWithCaptionsExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="crossfade">Crossfade</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Create smooth transitions between slides using the crossfade effect. Add the <code
                >carousel-fade</code
              >
              class alongside <code>carousel slide</code> to enable this elegant transition style. Instead
              of sliding horizontally, slides will fade in and out.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Carousel with Crossfade"
              height="450px"
              component={carouselCrossfadeExample}
              htmlCode={carouselCrossfadeExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="autoplaying-carousels">Autoplaying Carousels</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Enable automatic cycling through slides by adding <code>data-bs-ride="carousel"</code
              >. This creates a hands-free slideshow that begins cycling automatically when the page
              loads. Users can still interact with the navigation controls to manually advance
              slides.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Autoplaying Carousel"
              height="450px"
              component={autoplayCarouselExample}
              htmlCode={autoplayCarouselExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />

            <p class="py-2">
              For user-triggered carousels, use <code>data-bs-ride="true"</code>. This option starts
              the carousel cycling only after the first user interaction, providing a more
              controlled experience.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="User-Triggered Carousel"
              height="450px"
              component={userTriggeredCarouselExample}
              htmlCode={userTriggeredCarouselExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="individual-item-interval">Individual Slide Intervals</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Customize the display duration for individual slides using the <code
                >data-bs-interval</code
              > attribute. Set different time intervals (in milliseconds) for each slide to control how
              long they remain visible before transitioning to the next slide.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Individual Slide Intervals"
              height="450px"
              component={individualIntervalCarouselExample}
              htmlCode={individualIntervalCarouselExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="autoplaying-carousels-without-controls">
              Autoplaying Without Controls
            </h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Create a simplified carousel that automatically cycles through slides without
              navigation controls. This version is ideal for displaying content in a continuous loop
              where user interaction isn't needed or desired.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Autoplay Without Controls"
              height="450px"
              component={noControlsCarouselExample}
              htmlCode={noControlsCarouselExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="disable-touch-swiping">Disable Touch Swiping</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Disable touch-based navigation by adding <code>data-bs-touch="false"</code> to the carousel.
              This prevents users from swiping between slides on touch-enabled devices, limiting navigation
              to the control buttons only.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Disable Touch Swiping"
              height="450px"
              component={noTouchCarouselExample}
              htmlCode={noTouchCarouselExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <Toc />
  </div>
</AdminLayout>
